a2SystemPrimaryUserName.description: The name of the primary user or owner of this system.

a2SystemBootupTime.name: a2SystemBootupTime

a2SystemDateTime.name: a2SystemDateTime

a4BiosIndex.name: a4BiosIndex
a4BiosIndex.description: The index into the system BIOS table.

a4BiosManufacturer.name: a4BiosManufacturer
a4BiosManufacturer.description: The name of the company that wrote this System BIOS.

a4BiosVersion.name: a4BiosVersion
a4BiosVersion.description: The version number or version string of this BIOS.

a4BiosRomSize.name: a4BiosRomSize
a4BiosRomSize.description: The physical size of this BIOS ROM device in kilobytes.

a4BiosStartingAddress.name: a4BiosStartingAddress
a4BiosStartingAddress.description: The starting physical address for the memory which the BIOS occupies.

a4BiosEndingAddress.name: a4BiosEndingAddress

a4BiosLoaderVersion.name: a4BiosLoaderVersion
a4BiosLoaderVersion.description: The BIOS flash loader version number or string.

a4PrimaryBios.name: a4PrimaryBios

a5BiosCharacteristicDescription.name: a5BiosCharacteristicDescription
a5BiosCharacteristicDescription.description: An expanded description of this BIOS Characteristic.

a6ProcessorType.description: The type of processor currently in the system.

a6ProcessorFamily.name: a6ProcessorFamily

a6ProcessorVersionInformation.name: a6ProcessorVersionInformation
a6ProcessorVersionInformation.description: The version number or string for this processor.

a6MaximumSpeed.name: a6MaximumSpeed
a6MaximumSpeed.description: The maximum speed (in MHz) of this processor.

a6CurrentSpeed.name: a6CurrentSpeed
a6CurrentSpeed.description: The current speed (in MHz) of this processor.

a6ProcessorUpgrade.name: a6ProcessorUpgrade
a6ProcessorUpgrade.description: The method by which this processor can be upgraded, if upgrades aresupported.

a6FruGroupIndex.name: a6FruGroupIndex
a6FruGroupIndex.description: If this is a Field Replaceable Unit or if it is part of another FRU, thisprovides an index into the FRU table; 'value = -1' indicates that the group is not a FRU.

a6OperationalGroupIndex.name: a6OperationalGroupIndex
a6OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State Table for this device if applicable.

a6Level1CacheIndex.name: a6Level1CacheIndex
a6Level1CacheIndex.description: An index into the System Cache table that identifies the entrythat describes the L1 cache for this processor. If more than oneprocessor points to the same cache entry this means they sharethat cache.

a6Level2CacheIndex.name: a6Level2CacheIndex
a6Level2CacheIndex.description: An index into the System Cache table that identifies the entrythat describes the L2 cache for this processor If more than oneprocessor points to the same cache entry this means they sharethat cache.

a6Level3CacheIndex.name: a6Level3CacheIndex
a6Level3CacheIndex.description: An index into the System Cache table that identifies the entrythat describes the L3 cache for this processor. If more than oneprocessor points to the same cache entry this means they sharethat cache.

tMotherboard.name: tMotherboard
tMotherboard.description: This group defines attributes for the motherboard.

a7NumberOfExpansionSlots.description: The total number of expansion slots which physically exist on themotherboard whether occupied or not (see System Slots group).

a7FruGroupIndex.name: a7FruGroupIndex

a7OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State Table for this device if applicable.

a10SystemCacheIndex.description: An index into the System Cache table.

a10SystemCacheLevel.name: a10SystemCacheLevel
a10SystemCacheLevel.description: Is this the primary System Cache, or a subsidiary cache?

a10SystemCacheSpeed.name: a10SystemCacheSpeed
a10SystemCacheSpeed.description: The speed of this System Cache module in nanoseconds.

a10SystemCacheSize.name: a10SystemCacheSize
a10SystemCacheSize.description: The size of this System Cache module in kilobytes.

a10SystemCacheWritePolicy.name: a10SystemCacheWritePolicy
a10SystemCacheWritePolicy.description: Is this a write-back or a write-through cache?

a10SystemCacheErrorCorrection.name: a10SystemCacheErrorCorrection
a10SystemCacheErrorCorrection.description: The error correction scheme supported by this cache component.

a10FruGroupIndex.name: a10FruGroupIndex
a10FruGroupIndex.description: If this is a Field Replaceable Unit or if it is part of another FRU, thisprovides an index into the FRU table; 'value = -1' indicates that the group is not a FRU.

a10OperationalGroupIndex.name: a10OperationalGroupIndex
a10OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State Table for this device.

a10SystemCacheType.name: a10SystemCacheType
a10SystemCacheType.description: This defines the system cache type.

tPowerSupply.name: tPowerSupply
tPowerSupply.description: This group defines various attributes for power supplies in this system.

a17PowerSupplyIndex.name: a17PowerSupplyIndex
a17PowerSupplyIndex.description: The index number of the current power supply.

a17FruGroupIndex.name: a17FruGroupIndex
a17FruGroupIndex.description: If this is a Field Replaceable Unit or if it is part of another FRU, thisprovides an index into the FRU table; 'value = -1' indicates that the group is not a FRU.

a17OperationalGroupIndex.name: a17OperationalGroupIndex
a17OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State table for this device.

a17PowerUnitIndex.name: a17PowerUnitIndex
a17PowerUnitIndex.description: This is the ID of the Power Unit (logical power supply) to which thisPower Supply belongs. This value matches up with the Power Unit Table Indexattribute defined in the Power Unit Globe Table.

a17PowerSupplyType.name: a17PowerSupplyType
a17PowerSupplyType.description: This attribute describes the type of Power Supply, e.g. Linear, Switching, Battery, etc.

a17InputVoltageCapabilityDescription.name: a17InputVoltageCapabilityDescription
a17InputVoltageCapabilityDescription.description: An expanded description of the Input Voltage Capability for this PowerSupply.

a17Range1InputVoltageLow.name: a17Range1InputVoltageLow
a17Range1InputVoltageLow.description: The low voltage of Input Voltage Range 1 for this Power Supply, inmillivolts. A value of 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a17Range1InputVoltageHigh.name: a17Range1InputVoltageHigh
a17Range1InputVoltageHigh.description: The high voltage of Input Voltage Range 1 for this Power Supply, inmillivolts. A value of 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a17Range1VoltageProbeIndex.name: a17Range1VoltageProbeIndex
a17Range1VoltageProbeIndex.description: Index into the Voltage Probe table identifying the voltage probemonitoring this input range. 0 indicates no probe provided.

a17Range1ElectricalCurrentProbeIndex.name: a17Range1ElectricalCurrentProbeIndex
a17Range1ElectricalCurrentProbeIndex.description: Index into the Elelctrical Current Probe table identifying the Electrical current probe monitoring this input range. 0 indicates no probe provided.

a17Range2InputVoltageLow.name: a17Range2InputVoltageLow
a17Range2InputVoltageLow.description: The low voltage of Input Voltage Range 2 for this Power Supply, inmillivolts. A value of 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a17Range2InputVoltageHigh.name: a17Range2InputVoltageHigh
a17Range2InputVoltageHigh.description: The high voltage of Input Voltage Range 2 for this Power Supply, inmillivolts. A value of 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'

a17Range2VoltageProbeIndex.name: a17Range2VoltageProbeIndex
a17Range2VoltageProbeIndex.description: Index into the Voltage Probe table identifying the voltage probemonitoring this input range. 0 indicates no probe provided.

a17Range2CurrentProbeIndex.name: a17Range2CurrentProbeIndex
a17Range2CurrentProbeIndex.description: Index into the Current Probe table identifying the current probemonitoring this input range. 0 indicates no probe provided.

a17ActiveInputVoltageRange.name: a17ActiveInputVoltageRange
a17ActiveInputVoltageRange.description: The value of this attribute indicates which input voltage range of thisPower Supply is currently active.

a17InputVoltageRangeSwitching.name: a17InputVoltageRangeSwitching
a17InputVoltageRangeSwitching.description: This attribute describes the kind of input voltage range switching that isimplemented in this power supply.

a17Range1InputFrequencyLow.name: a17Range1InputFrequencyLow
a17Range1InputFrequencyLow.description: The frequency at the low end of this power supply's Input FrequencyRange 1. A value of zero implies DC. A value of 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'

a17Range1InputFrequencyHigh.name: a17Range1InputFrequencyHigh
a17Range1InputFrequencyHigh.description: The frequency at the high end of this power supply's Input FrequencyRange 1. A value of zero implies DC. A value of 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'

a17Range2InputFrequencyLow.name: a17Range2InputFrequencyLow
a17Range2InputFrequencyLow.description: The frequency at the low end of this power supply's Input FrequencyRange 2. A value of zero implies DC. A value of 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'

a17Range2InputFrequencyHigh.name: a17Range2InputFrequencyHigh
a17Range2InputFrequencyHigh.description: The frequency at the high end of this power supply's Input FrequencyRange 2. A value of zero implies DC. A value of 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'

a17TotalOutputPower.name: a17TotalOutputPower
a17TotalOutputPower.description: This attribute value represents the total output power of this powersupply in milliWatts. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'

tSystemSlots.name: tSystemSlots
tSystemSlots.description: This group defines the attributes for the different system expansion slotssupportedin this system.

a19SlotIndex.name: a19SlotIndex
a19SlotIndex.description: An index into the system slot table. This is the hardware ID number foreach expansion slot, whether it is occupied or not (starting with 1).

a19SlotType.name: a19SlotType
a19SlotType.description: The bus type supported in this slot. This is a bit field with the followingdefinitions: Bit 0 (2^0), if set, means it is a long-length card; if 0, it is a short-length card, Bit 1(2^1), if set, indicates ISA, Bit 2 (2^2) indicates EISA, Bit 3 (2^3) indicates MCA, Bit 4 (2^4) indicates PCI, Bit 5 (2^5) indicates VL,Bit 6 (2^6) indicates PCMCIA, Bit (2^7) refers to NuBus, Bit 8 (2^8) indicates PC-98/C20, Bit 9 (2^9) indicates PC-98/C24, Bit 10 (2^10) indicates PC-98/E, Bit 11 (2^11) indicates PC-98/Local

a19SlotWidth.name: a19SlotWidth
a19SlotWidth.description: The maximum bus width of cards accepted in this slot.

a19CurrentUsage.name: a19CurrentUsage
a19CurrentUsage.description: Is this slot is currently in use?

a19SlotDescription.name: a19SlotDescription
a19SlotDescription.description: The card currently occupying this slot.

a19SlotCategory.name: a19SlotCategory
a19SlotCategory.description: The word 'slot' is used to refer to bus slots. The last case (motherboard)refers to situations where a functional element is integrated onto, say, a motherboardand connects to a bus without a connector. It still takes up an expansion site on the busbut this is termed a 'virtual slot' as opposed to a physical slot (see the attribute 'VirtualSlot'). Virtual slots are in effect permanently occupied expansion sites. This attributeestablis es which category of physical slot this table entry is defining.

a19VirtualSlot.name: a19VirtualSlot
a19VirtualSlot.description: This attribute indicates whether this is a 'virtual slot' or not. A 'virtualslot' is an expansion site that is permanently occupied because of the level ofintegration of an expandable component. An example of a virtual slot is an I/O busposition taken up by a LAN controller that is integrated onto a motherboard. A slot withthe 'Slot Category' of Motherboard is typically a Virtual Slot.

a19ResourceUserId.name: a19ResourceUserId
a19ResourceUserId.description: Value used to locate the rows in the System Resources 2 table forthe resources associated with this slot or expansion site. 0 = 'unspecified'.

a19VccMixedVoltageSupport.name: a19VccMixedVoltageSupport
a19VccMixedVoltageSupport.description: Device Vcc Mixed Voltage support. This is a bit field with the following definitions: Bit 0 (2^0), if set, indicates 3.3V support Bit 1 (2^1), if set, indicates 5V support

a19VppMixedVoltageSupport.name: a19VppMixedVoltageSupport
a19VppMixedVoltageSupport.description: Device Vpp Mixed Voltage support. This is a bit field with the following definitions: Bit 0 (2^0), if set, indicates 3.3V support Bit 1 (2^1), if set, indicates 5V support Bit 2 (2^2), if set, indicates 12V support

a19SlotThermalRating.name: a19SlotThermalRating
a19SlotThermalRating.description: The maximum thermal dissipation of the slot in milliwatts.

a19OperationalGroupIndex.name: a19OperationalGroupIndex
a19OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State table for this device.

a19SlotPowerState.name: a19SlotPowerState
a19SlotPowerState.description: The current state of the PHP system slot.

a19SlotFaultState.name: a19SlotFaultState
a19SlotFaultState.description: The current error state for the PHP system slot.

tCoolingUnitGlobalTable.name: tCoolingUnitGlobalTable
tCoolingUnitGlobalTable.description: This global table describes all of the Cooling Units in this system component. The unique index of each Cooling Unit is a key into this table. A Cooling Unit is composed of potentially more than one Cooling Device in a redundant configuration. Cooling devices are described by the 'Cooling Device' standard group. Each cooling device described by a row in the Cooling Device standard group will point to a corresponding Cooling Unit in this table by using the row index of the row that describes the Coolin

a28CoolingUnitIndex.name: a28CoolingUnitIndex
a28CoolingUnitIndex.description: The unique index given to each Cooling Unit being described by this table. This unique index is the key into this table.

a28CoolingUnitStatus.name: a28CoolingUnitStatus
a28CoolingUnitStatus.description: Gives the redundancy status of the Cooling Unit. 'Fully Redundan ' means that all of the configured redundancy is still available; 'Degraded Redundancy' means that some failures have been experienced but some reduced amount of redundancy is still available; 'Redundancy Lost' means that a sufficie t number of failures have been experienced that no redundancy is available and the next failure experienced within the Cooling Unit will cause overall Cooling Unit failure.

tFieldReplaceableUnit.name: tFieldReplaceableUnit
tFieldReplaceableUnit.description: A Field Replaceable Unit (FRU), is defined as a hardware componentwhich is designed to be separately removable for replacement or repair. For thepurposes of this definition, a motherboard and a fixed hard disk are FRUs, whereas afixed hard disk platter or a chip fixed in place on the motherboard are not FRUs sincethey are not designed to be separately removable. Each instance within the FRU tableshould contain the device group and instance data for the associated hardwarecomponent.

a30FruIndex.name: a30FruIndex
a30FruIndex.description: The index into the Field Replaceable Unit table.

a30DeviceGroupIndex.name: a30DeviceGroupIndex
a30DeviceGroupIndex.description: The group ID of the group referencing this Field Replaceable Unitinstance.

a30Description.name: a30Description
a30Description.description: A clear description of this Field Replaceable Unit.

a30Manufacturer.name: a30Manufacturer
a30Manufacturer.description: The name of the company manufacturing or providing this FieldRep aceableUnit.

a30Model.name: a30Model
a30Model.description: The manufacturer's model number for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a30PartNumber.name: a30PartNumber
a30PartNumber.description: A part number by which a replacement part can be ordered for this FieldReplaceable Unit.

a30FruSerialNumber.name: a30FruSerialNumber
a30FruSerialNumber.description: The manufacturer's serial number for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a30RevisionLevel.name: a30RevisionLevel
a30RevisionLevel.description: The revision level of this Field Replaceable Unit.

a30WarrantyStartDate.name: a30WarrantyStartDate
a30WarrantyStartDate.description: The start date of the service warranty for this Field Replaceabl Unit.

a30WarrantyDuration.name: a30WarrantyDuration
a30WarrantyDuration.description: The total duration of this Field Replaceable Unit warranty in months.

a30SupportPhoneNumber.name: a30SupportPhoneNumber
a30SupportPhoneNumber.description: The phone number(s) for support for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a30FruInternetUniformResourceLocator.name: a30FruInternetUniformResourceLocator
a30FruInternetUniformResourceLocator.description: The Internet Uniform Resource Locator string that can be used through a World Wide Web browser to obtain further information about this FRU

tOperationalState.name: tOperationalState
tOperationalState.description: This group provides the operational state, usage, and availabili y status,and administrative state indicators for specific Device Group instances

a31OperationalStateInstanceIndex.name: a31OperationalStateInstanceIndex
a31OperationalStateInstanceIndex.description: The Index into the Operational State table.

a31DeviceGroupIndex.name: a31DeviceGroupIndex
a31DeviceGroupIndex.description: The group ID of the group referencing this instance.

a31OperationalStatus.name: a31OperationalStatus
a31OperationalStatus.description: The operational status of the Device Group instance.

a31UsageState.name: a31UsageState
a31UsageState.description: The usage state of the Device Group instance.

a31AvailabilityStatus.name: a31AvailabilityStatus
a31AvailabilityStatus.description: The availability status of the Device Group instance.

a31AdministrativeState.name: a31AdministrativeState
a31AdministrativeState.description: The administrative state of the Device Group instance.

a31FatalErrorCount.name: a31FatalErrorCount
a31FatalErrorCount.description: The accumulated Fatal or Non-recoverable error count for this Device Group instance.

a31MajorErrorCount.name: a31MajorErrorCount
a31MajorErrorCount.description: The accumulated Major or Critical error count for this Device Group instance.

a31WarningErrorCount.name: a31WarningErrorCount
a31WarningErrorCount.description: The accumulated Warning or Non-Critical error count for this Device Group instance.

a31CurrentErrorStatus.name: a31CurrentErrorStatus
a31CurrentErrorStatus.description: This attribute presents the current error status for this Device Group instance. The most critical error status in effect should be presented. I.e. if a part of the Device Group instance is 'Critical', while other status is 'Non-critical' then the status'Critical' should be reported.

a31DevicePredictedFailureStatus.name: a31DevicePredictedFailureStatus
a31DevicePredictedFailureStatus.description: Enumeration describing the current Device Predicted Failure Status (e.g.: the S.M.A.R.T. status of the device).

tPhysicalMemoryArray.name: tPhysicalMemoryArray
tPhysicalMemoryArray.description: This group represents an array of physical memory as a collectio ofone or more Memory Devices associated in sets and partitions.

a34MemoryArrayTableIndex.name: a34MemoryArrayTableIndex
a34MemoryArrayTableIndex.description: A unique number that identifies this row.

a34MemoryArrayLocation.name: a34MemoryArrayLocation
a34MemoryArrayLocation.description: The physical location of the Memory Array, whether on the systemboard or an add-on board.

a34MemoryArrayUse.name: a34MemoryArrayUse
a34MemoryArrayUse.description: What this Memory Array is used for.

a34MaximumMemoryCapacity.name: a34MaximumMemoryCapacity
a34MaximumMemoryCapacity.description: The maximum memory capacity, in kilobytes, on this array. 0x80000000denotes 'unknown'.

a34NumberOfMemoryDeviceSockets.name: a34NumberOfMemoryDeviceSockets
a34NumberOfMemoryDeviceSockets.description: The number of SIMM slots or sockets available for Memory Devices inthis array. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a34NumberOfMemoryDeviceSocketsUsed.name: a34NumberOfMemoryDeviceSocketsUsed
a34NumberOfMemoryDeviceSocketsUsed.description: The number of SIMM slots or sockets in use for Memory Devices in thisarray. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a34MemoryErrorCorrection.name: a34MemoryErrorCorrection
a34MemoryErrorCorrection.description: The main hardware error correction or detection method supported bythis Memory Array.

a34ArrayErrorType.name: a34ArrayErrorType
a34ArrayErrorType.description: The type of error that is associated with the current status reported inOperational State for this Memory Array.

a34LastErrorUpdate.name: a34LastErrorUpdate
a34LastErrorUpdate.description: System state during which last error status was collected.

a34ErrorOperation.name: a34ErrorOperation
a34ErrorOperation.description: The memory access operation that caused the current error.

a34ErrorDataSize.name: a34ErrorDataSize
a34ErrorDataSize.description: The size of the data transfer that caused the error, in bits. Zero indicatesno error, 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a34ErrorData.name: a34ErrorData
a34ErrorData.description: Data captured during the erroneous Memory Array access. The dataoccupy the first n bytes of the octetstring required to hold 'Error Data Size' bits of thedata. Data are stored least-significant byte first.

a34VendorSyndrome.name: a34VendorSyndrome
a34VendorSyndrome.description: Vendor-specific syndrome or CRC data associated with the erroneousaccess.

a34ErrorAddress.name: a34ErrorAddress
a34ErrorAddress.description: Physical address of the error based on the addressing of the bus that theMemory Array is connected to. 0x8000 0000 0000 0000 denotes 'unknown'.

a34ErrorResolution.name: a34ErrorResolution
a34ErrorResolution.description: Range in bytes that the error can be determined to be within, when anError Address is given. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a34FruGroupIndex.name: a34FruGroupIndex
a34FruGroupIndex.description: If this is a Field Replaceable Unit or if it is part of another FRU, thisprovides an index into the FRU table; 'value = -1' indicates that the group is not aFRU.

a34OperationalGroupIndex.name: a34OperationalGroupIndex
a34OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State Table for this Memory Array. TheOperational State row is used to hold the overall error count and error status for thisarray.

tMemoryArrayMappedAddresses.name: tMemoryArrayMappedAddresses
tMemoryArrayMappedAddresses.description: This table presents ranges of physical addresses that are mapped to agiven Memory Array.

a35MemoryArrayMappedAddressesTableIndex.name: a35MemoryArrayMappedAddressesTableIndex
a35MemoryArrayMappedAddressesTableIndex.description: A unique number that identifies this row.

a35MemoryArrayIndex.name: a35MemoryArrayIndex
a35MemoryArrayIndex.description: The ID of the Memory Array that this address range is mapped to.Multiple address ranges may be mapped to a Memory Array.

a35MappedRangeStartingAddress.name: a35MappedRangeStartingAddress
a35MappedRangeStartingAddress.description: The physical starting address, in kilobytes, of a range of memorymapped to the specified Memory Array. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a35MappedRangeEndingAddress.name: a35MappedRangeEndingAddress
a35MappedRangeEndingAddress.description: The physical ending address of the last kilobyte of a range of addressesmapped to the specified Memory Array. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a35PartitionId.name: a35PartitionId
a35PartitionId.description: Identifies a Memory Partition associated with the Memory Arrayspecified by Memory Array Table Index. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a35PartitionWidth.name: a35PartitionWidth
a35PartitionWidth.description: The number of Memory Devices that form a single row of memory forthe partition. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a35OperationalGroupIndex.name: a35OperationalGroupIndex
a35OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State Table for this Memory Range.Generally, there will be a 1:1 correspondence between a mapped range and a partition.In which case, the Operational State will be for the partition as well. In the case thatthere is more than one mapped range for a partion, it will be necessary to check theOperational State entries for each range to determine the overall status of the partition.

tMemoryDevice.name: tMemoryDevice
tMemoryDevice.description: This group presents information about individual memory devices in thesystem. A memory device can be a SIMM, a SIPP, or a single chip, or an entire card -based on the resolution to which a memory error can be determine and whether thedevice is replaceable as a unit.

a36MemoryDeviceTableIndex.name: a36MemoryDeviceTableIndex
a36MemoryDeviceTableIndex.description: A unique number that identifies this row.

a36MemoryArrayIndex.name: a36MemoryArrayIndex
a36MemoryArrayIndex.description: The ID of the Memory Array that this Memory Device is a part of.

a36DeviceLocator.name: a36DeviceLocator
a36DeviceLocator.description: A string identifying the physically labeled socket or board positionwhere the memory device is located. Eg. 'SIMM 3' or 'IC12'.

a36BankLocator.name: a36BankLocator
a36BankLocator.description: A string identifying the physically labeled bank where the memorydevice is located. Eg. 'Bank 0' or 'A'.

a36Size.name: a36Size
a36Size.description: Size of this memory device, in bytes.

a36FormFactor.name: a36FormFactor
a36FormFactor.description: Implementation form factor for this memory device.

a36TotalWidth.name: a36TotalWidth
a36TotalWidth.description: Total width of this memory device, including check or error correctionbits, in bits. If there are no error correction bits, the value in this attribute should matchthat specified in Data Width. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a36DataWidth.name: a36DataWidth
a36DataWidth.description: Data width of this memory device, in bits. A data width of 0 and a TotalWidth of 8 would indicate that the device is solely being used to provide eight errorcorrection bits. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a36MemoryType.name: a36MemoryType
a36MemoryType.description: Type of memory used in this memory device.

a36TypeDetail.name: a36TypeDetail
a36TypeDetail.description: Additional detail on the device type.

a36DeviceSet.name: a36DeviceSet
a36DeviceSet.description: This attribute is used to identify when the Memory Device is one of a setof Memory Devices that must be populated with all devices of the same type and size, and which set the device belongs to. For example, when one SIMM belongs to a set offour. 0 indicates the Memory Device isn't part of a set. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a36DeviceErrorType.name: a36DeviceErrorType
a36DeviceErrorType.description: The type of error that is associated with the current status reported inOperational State for this Memory Device.

a36ErrorGranularity.name: a36ErrorGranularity
a36ErrorGranularity.description: Specifies whether the current error's location can be resolved to thepartition or device level.

a36LastErrorUpdate.name: a36LastErrorUpdate
a36LastErrorUpdate.description: System state during which the last error update was collected.

a36ErrorOperation.name: a36ErrorOperation
a36ErrorOperation.description: The memory access operation that caused the current error.

a36ErrorDataSize.name: a36ErrorDataSize
a36ErrorDataSize.description: The size of the data transfer that caused the error,in bits. Zero indicatesno error, 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a36ErrorData.name: a36ErrorData
a36ErrorData.description: Data captured during the erroneous Memory Array access. The dataoccupies the first n bytes of the octetstring required to hold 'Error Data Size' bits of thedata. Data is stored least-significant byte first.

a36VendorSyndrome.name: a36VendorSyndrome
a36VendorSyndrome.description: Vendor-specific syndrome or CRC data associated withthe erroneou access.

a36DeviceErrorAddress.name: a36DeviceErrorAddress
a36DeviceErrorAddress.description: Physical address of the error relative to the start of the device, in bytes.0x80000000 denotes 'unknown'.

a36ArrayErrorAddress.name: a36ArrayErrorAddress

tSystemControl.name: tSystemControl
tSystemControl.description: Status and control of global system control features.

a1004Selfid.name: a1004Selfid
a1004Selfid.description: A unique number that identifies this row.

a1004ResetSystem.name: a1004ResetSystem
a1004ResetSystem.description: Writing to this attribute with a properly authenticated challenge hash string initiates an immediate system hard reset. Reading this value is undefined.

a1004TimedResetIncrement.name: a1004TimedResetIncrement
a1004TimedResetIncrement.description: This attribute contains the increments in which a timed reset can be set, in microseconds.

a1004TimedResetResolution.name: a1004TimedResetResolution
a1004TimedResetResolution.description: This attribute contains the resolution to which a Timed Reset can be set, in microseconds. For example, a resolution of 1 second and an increment of 10 seconds would indicate that a 10 second delay interval setting produces a 9 to 10 second delay.

a1004TimeUntilSystemReset.name: a1004TimeUntilSystemReset
a1004TimeUntilSystemReset.description: This attribute contains the interval for timed resets, in units of the Timed Reset Increment attribute. Writing a non-zero value, and setting the Timed Reset Enable on, initiates a timed reset countdown.

a1004SystemPowerCapabilities.name: a1004SystemPowerCapabilities
a1004SystemPowerCapabilities.description: This attribute describes the system power control capabilities. It can have one of the following values: Unknown, On And Off, Off Only, or On Only.

a1004SystemPowerStatus.name: a1004SystemPowerStatus
a1004SystemPowerStatus.description: This attribute provides access to the status of system power. Its value is either On or Off.

a1004EventLoggingCapability.name: a1004EventLoggingCapability
a1004EventLoggingCapability.description: This attribute describes the Event Logging Capabilities. The attribute value can be : Unknown, Unsupported, Active, or Inactive. If the Event logging capability is Active, the BIOS logs the system errors to the FLASH. The LSC reads this FLASH log and takes appropriate actions. If this feature is Inactive, the LSC will read the values from the system registers directly. The Event logging capability can be set to Active or Inactive using the System Configuration Utility (SCU).

a1004WatchdogTimerIncrement.name: a1004WatchdogTimerIncrement
a1004WatchdogTimerIncrement.description: This attribute contains the increments in which a watchdog update interval can be set. This value is maintained internally by instrumentat on code in microseconds. In LSC Local Console, this value is shown in Seconds.

a1004WatchdogTimerResolution.name: a1004WatchdogTimerResolution
a1004WatchdogTimerResolution.description: Resolution to which a watchdog update interval can be set. For example, a watchdog timer resolution of R microsecond and an watchdog timer increment of I microseconds would indicate that a watchdog update interval setting of N will produce a (N*I)-R to (N*I) microseconds delay. In LSC Local Console, this value is shown in Seconds.

a1004WatchdogUpdateInterval.name: a1004WatchdogUpdateInterval
a1004WatchdogUpdateInterval.description: This attribute specifies the Interval for watchdog resets, in minutes. If the system software does not update the watchdog timer within this interval, a hard reset will occur. Selecting a non-zero value for this attribute and setting the Use System Watchdog Feature attribute to 'On' starts the watchdog reset timer countdown.

a1004UseSystemWatchdogFeature.name: a1004UseSystemWatchdogFeature
a1004UseSystemWatchdogFeature.description: If this value is On, then the Watchdog feature is enabled and the Watchdog Update Interval value is valid. If enabled this feature automatically resets the server if the LSC software does not reset the watchdog timer within the specified Watchdog Update Interval. NOTE : This is a hard reset that will immediately reset the system without taking NetWare down. This might result in some files being corrupted.

a1004ResetSystemAfterDelay.name: a1004ResetSystemAfterDelay
a1004ResetSystemAfterDelay.description: Writing to this attribute with a properly authenticated challenge hash string will initiate a timed reset, the reset will occur when the Timed Reset Interval expires. Reading this attribute will have undefined results.

a1004SavePersistentData.name: a1004SavePersistentData
a1004SavePersistentData.description: When this attribute value is set to ON all the persistent data like thresholds are stored into the persistent data Table.

a1004RestoreFactoryDefaults.name: a1004RestoreFactoryDefaults
a1004RestoreFactoryDefaults.description: Writing to this attribute with a properly authenticated challenge hash string will cause all the Factory default thresholds to be restored. Reading this attribute will have undefined results.

a1004ShutdownOs.name: a1004ShutdownOs
a1004ShutdownOs.description: Writing to this attribute with a properly authenticated challenge hash string will initiate an immediate OS shutdown Reading this attribute will have undefined results.

a1004ShutdownOsAndPowerOff.name: a1004ShutdownOsAndPowerOff
a1004ShutdownOsAndPowerOff.description: Writing to this attribute with a properly authenticated challenge hash string will initiate an immediate OS shutdown and power off of the system. Reading this attribute will have undefined results.

a1004ShutdownOsAndHardwareReset.name: a1004ShutdownOsAndHardwareReset
a1004ShutdownOsAndHardwareReset.description: Writing to this attribute with a properly authenticated challenge hash string will initiate an immediate OS shutdown and hardware reset of the system. Reading this attribute will have undefined results.

a1004IssueAHardwareNmi.name: a1004IssueAHardwareNmi
a1004IssueAHardwareNmi.description: Writing to this attribute with a properly authenticated challenge hash string will initiate an immediate hardware NMI. Reading this attribute will have undefined results.

a1004ImmediatePowerDown.name: a1004ImmediatePowerDown
a1004ImmediatePowerDown.description: Writing to this attribute with a properly authenticated challenge hash string initiates an immediate power off the system. Reading this value is undefined.

a1004Challenge.name: a1004Challenge
a1004Challenge.description: Reading this value will return a challenge string that may be hashed with the firmware (DPC) password and then written to any of the authenticated attributes to perform a desired action. Once issued the challenge string will only be valid for a short time and may only be used once.

a1004VerifyPrivilege.name: a1004VerifyPrivilege
a1004VerifyPrivilege.description: Writing to this attribute with a properly authenticated challenge hash string will result in a successful write operation. Reading this value is undefined.

tCoolingSensors.description: This table contains one row for each cooling fan in the system. Each row contains the status and control information for a single fan.

a1005Selfid.name: a1005Selfid
a1005Selfid.description: A unique number that identifies this row.

a1005OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State table for this device.

a1005CoolingDeviceType.name: a1005CoolingDeviceType
a1005CoolingDeviceType.description: This attribute describes the fan type. It has one of the following values: Muffin, Axial, Piezo, or Squirrel Cage.

a1005CfmRating.name: a1005CfmRating
a1005CfmRating.description: This attribute presents the maximum CFM rating of this fan.

a1005FanUnits.name: a1005FanUnits
a1005FanUnits.description: This attribute describes the units of fan status measurement. It has one of the following values: RPM, CFM, or OK/Fatal.

a1005MaximumReading.name: a1005MaximumReading
a1005MaximumReading.description: This attribute contains the highest reading supported on this fan's sensor, measured in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute. This attribute may not apply to all fan types.

a1005MinimumReading.name: a1005MinimumReading
a1005MinimumReading.description: This attribute contains the lowest reading supported on this fan's sensor, measured in the units specified Fan Units attribute. This attribute may not apply to all fan types.

a1005CurrentReading.name: a1005CurrentReading
a1005CurrentReading.description: This attribute contains the current fan sensor reading, measured in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute. This attribute will display as Unsupported if the hardware does not support this feature.

a1005SensorAccuracy.name: a1005SensorAccuracy
a1005SensorAccuracy.description: This attribute describes the sensor's accuracy in +/- hundredth of a percent.

a1005SensorTolerancePlus.name: a1005SensorTolerancePlus
a1005SensorTolerancePlus.description: This attribute describes the sensor's '+' tolerance in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute.

a1005SensorToleranceMinus.name: a1005SensorToleranceMinus
a1005SensorToleranceMinus.description: This attribute describes the sensor's '-' tolerance in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute.

a1005Non_criticalThreshold.name: a1005Non_criticalThreshold
a1005Non_criticalThreshold.description: This attribute contains the warning threshold level for the fan. The threshold is given in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute.

a1005CriticalThreshold.name: a1005CriticalThreshold
a1005CriticalThreshold.description: This attribute contains the major error threshold level for the fan. The threshold is given in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute.

a1005Non_recoverableThreshold.name: a1005Non_recoverableThreshold
a1005Non_recoverableThreshold.description: This attribute contains the fatal error threshold level for the fan. The threshold is given in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute.

a1005CoolingSensorDescription.name: a1005CoolingSensorDescription
a1005CoolingSensorDescription.description: Additional descriptive information about the Cooling sensor orsensor's location.

a1005NominalReading.name: a1005NominalReading
a1005NominalReading.description: Nominal reading for this fan, in units. 80000000h indicates that this attribute is not supported.

a1005LowestNormalReading.name: a1005LowestNormalReading
a1005LowestNormalReading.description: Specified lowest normal reading for this fan, in units. Readings beyond this value indicate an abnormal condition. 80000000h indicates that this attribute is not supported.

a1005HighestNormalReading.name: a1005HighestNormalReading
a1005HighestNormalReading.description: Specified lowest normal reading for this fan, in units. Readings beyond this value indicate an abnormal condition. 80000000h indicates that this attribute is not supported.
